<br>
The Night Legion, an Army of Unsurpassed Mercenaries, is at present recruiting in this city. Several Vacancies still exist to complete the Night Legion’s complement of Soldiers and Officers.<br>
<br>
What Heart of Steel can resist an Appeal to Join this Band of Heroes and share the new Battles that await them? Who wishes for a Hatful of Coins as Plunder? There will be Fiddlers and Dancing Girls every evening; and Provisions, the Best of Beef, the Best of Grog; all in addition to the Pay under the Warrant of Commander Koruath! <br>
<br>
In the Place where this Notice is read can be found one of the Officers of the Night Legion who will enlist any Willing Hearts who Thirst for Glory!<br>
<br>
-----<br>
<br>
The Night Legion, currently recruiting. Contact Koruath, Kayriik, Shackleton or Nairda in game or visit the website: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub75.ezboard.com/bnightlegion">pub75.ezboard.com/bnightlegion</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
No, you won't be receiving any pay really<br>
<br>
----<br>
<br>
Charter<br>
<br>
1) The Night Legion has the following requirements for membership. You must be of at least 20th level. There is flexibility regarding alignment, but we are primarily a neutral guild. Applicants should bear in mind that the Night Legion is a mercenary army and thus their personal background should be consistent with a mercenary of some kind. At the current time, the application process is an informal one. Later, a formal application structure will be introduced.<br>
2) The Night Legion is divided into three battalions according to level, allowing the Night Legion to operate on several different tiers at any one time.<br>
3) The Night Legion uses a military-esque hierarchy with a system of promotion that will reward members in a variety of different ways. Although the hierarchy is quite strict, it is by no means a static hierarchy. There is sufficient flexibility to allow for significant advancement. If you are dedicated, you will over time be rewarded with increasing responsibility and status.<br>
4) The Night Legion encourages role-playing, particularly when using /say and through the IC channel /thelegion. However, role-playing is not compulsory. Be prepared to salute and be saluted. Guildchat is informal; technically, all comments there are Out Of Character by default.<br>
5) The Night Legion intends to undergo raids, and perhaps to one day reach the highest echelons of the game. However, The Night Legion is not a Racing Guild. We are only in competition with ourselves. As such, there are no rules regarding compulsory or minimum raid attendance and raiding will always be secondary to having fun. For the time being, loot will be distributed via an informal need before greed process, monitored by the officers.<br>
6) You are strongly encouraged to aid your fellow guild members, be it through quests, groups or help with equipment. <br>
7) The Night Legion supports Verant Interactive’s Play Nice Policy. Breaches of this will be met with disciplinary action.<br>
The Night Legion may at times go to War. This will always be in conjunction with the wishes of guild members, and all wars will be governed by our Rules of Engagement.<br>
